overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, aiming to validate its adherence to the provided Statement of
  Work and detailed specifications. The review identified several critical gaps,
  leading to a plan for implementation. The conversation then focused on
  executing this plan, starting with high-priority items. Key implementations
  included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference, complete
  with safety warnings for high scores. Additionally, the system was enhanced to
  detect and provide recommendations for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea
  (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. These changes required modifications
  to data types, validation logic, the interactive questionnaire UI, and both
  the on-screen and PDF-generated narrative reports, ensuring the application
  now provides more nuanced diagnostics and safety-critical information.
